title: Japanese billionaire cancels planned Starship lunar mission
summary: A Japanese billionaire who was the first commercial customer for SpaceX’s Starship vehicle has abruptly pulled the plug on his proposed quixotic circumlunar mission.

title: Starliner launch attempt scrubbed

title: Gyro Issues Force Hubble Into Safe Mode
summary: NASA’s Hubble Space Telescope has suspended science operations for the time being. NASA reported that the space observatory entered safe mode on May 24th.

title: Boeing, NASA cancel Starliner launch attempt scheduled Sunday after failed Saturday take-off
summary: Boeing’s first Starliner flight with astronauts on board was called off in the final minutes on Saturday, and the backup Sunday launch date was also canceled.

title: Blue Origin investigating New Shepard parachute issue
summary: A parachute failed to fully inflate on the latest Blue Origin New Shepard suborbital flight because a line controlling its expansion was not cut as planned.
